\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory requirements for uniquely identifying and authenticating all users,
 devices,
 and services prior to granting access to Elko County information systems and data.
 This policy ensures that all access is attributable to a verified identity,
 resistant to credential compromise,
 and compliant with FBI Criminal Justice Information Services (CJIS) Security Policy v6.0 and NIST SP 800-53 Rev.
 5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations (ECIO) personnel,
 County employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and any other entities accessing County IT resources.
 It governs all authenticators,
 including passwords,
 cryptographic tokens,
 smart cards,
 biometrics,
 device certificates,
 and service credentials used for local,
 network,
 remote,
 and application/API access.
\end_layout

