\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Unique Identification and Identifier Reuse
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unique Identification
\series default
:
 County systems shall uniquely identify each user.
 Assigning a single identifier to multiple individuals is prohibited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Shared/Generic Accounts
\series default
:
 Shared,
 generic,
 or group accounts are prohibited unless a Risk Acceptance Memo is approved in accordance with Section 4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Identifier Reuse Floor
\series default
:
 Identifiers (e.g.,
 usernames) shall not be reused for a minimum of one (1) year following account deactivation per CJIS IA-4(d).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 MFA Baselines and Authentication Strength
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
MFA Required for Restricted (Level 4)
\series default
:
 Multi-factor authentication (MFA) shall be required for access to Restricted data systems (CJI,
 PII,
 PHI),
 Restricted repositories,
 and administrative functions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
MFA Required for Remote and Privileged Access
\series default
:
 MFA shall be mandatory for all remote access and for privileged accounts consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 access control baselines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Replay-Resistant Requirement (CJI/AAL2)
\series default
:
 For access to CJI and workflows requiring replay resistance,
 at least one factor shall be replay-resistant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Authenticator Lifecycle and Revocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Identity Proofing
\series default
:
 HR shall conduct in-person identity verification prior to issuance of County credentials.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Revocation Timeframes
\series default
:
 ECIO shall disable accounts within twenty-four (24) hours for standard termination and within thirty (30) minutes for High-Risk Individuals as defined by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compromise/Loss Reporting
\series default
:
 Users shall report suspected authenticator compromise,
 loss,
 or theft immediately.
 If the authenticator or device provides access to CJI,
 reporting shall occur immediately and shall not exceed one (1) hour from discovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Temporary Authenticators
\series default
:
 Temporary authenticators (e.g.,
 initial passwords) shall require an immediate change to a user-defined secret upon first use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Rate Limiting and Unsuccessful Authentication
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Unsuccessful Logon Attempts
\series default
:
 Systems shall enforce unsuccessful logon attempt limits consistent with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 requirements:
 five (5) invalid attempts within a 15-minute period,
 resulting in a lockout until released by an administrator for CJI-connected systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Memorized Secret (Password) Standards
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Minimum Length
\series default
:
 Standard accounts shall require a minimum of twelve (12) characters.
 Privileged accounts (Tier L3+) shall require a minimum of fourteen (14) characters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Password History
\series default
:
 Systems shall prevent reuse of the last ten (10) passwords (County-defined standard).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Blocklist Screening
\series default
:
 Systems shall implement checks against commonly used and compromised passwords and shall update the reference data at least quarterly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compromise-Triggered Change
\series default
:
 Systems shall require password change upon evidence of compromise and shall not mandate periodic password changes as a primary control.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Service Accounts and API Credentials
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Interactive Logon Prohibited
\series default
:
 Service accounts shall not be used by personnel for administrative work or interactive logon.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Legacy Exception Controls
\series default
:
 If an application requires interactive use of a service account,
 the System Owner shall obtain a Risk Acceptance Memo that mandates:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Interactive enablement limited to maintenance windows
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
MFA for the interactive session
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Full event logging
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Secrets Management
\series default
:
 Service credentials and API keys shall be stored in an ECIO-approved secrets management solution and rotated upon suspected compromise or owner departure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Non-Organizational Users and Device Authentication
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Non-Organizational Users
\series default
:
 Contractors and vendors shall be uniquely identified and authenticated.
 Access shall be time-bounded and re-verified at least annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Device Identification
\series default
:
 County-managed devices shall be uniquely identified prior to network connection.
 Device authentication shall not substitute for user authentication or user MFA requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.8 Authentication Feedback
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Obscuration
\series default
:
 Systems shall mask characters during entry to protect against shoulder surfing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Generic Error Messages
\series default
:
 Authentication error messages shall be generic and shall not disclose which element of the credentials (username or password) was incorrect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.9 Mobile Device Advanced Authentication
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Requirement
\series default
:
 Mobile devices accessing CJI shall use advanced authentication (MFA) per 
\series bold
CJIS Section 5.20.7.2
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Compensating Controls
\series default
:
 Any mobile advanced-authentication exception shall require:
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
County MDM enrollment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Written CSO approval
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A documented expiration date
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.10 Public Key-Based Authentication (Smart Cards/Tokens)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Private Key Protection
\series default
:
 Systems implementing public key-based authentication (e.g.,
 HID DigitalPersona) shall enforce protection of the private key and prevent unauthorized use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Identity Mapping
\series default
:
 The authenticated identity shall be mapped to the unique individual account in the authoritative identity repository (e.g.,
 Active Directory).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Certificate Validation and Revocation
\series default
:
 Systems shall validate certificates to a trusted root and maintain revocation information (e.g.,
 CRL/OCSP) to support validation during network unavailability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.11 Cryptographic Protection (FIPS)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
FIPS Validation
\series default
:
 Cryptographic modules used to protect Restricted data shall be FIPS validated.
 FIPS 140-2 is acceptable until September 21,
 2026,
 after which FIPS 140-3 validation is mandatory.
\end_layout

